: Well..... WHAT?  Did any of those people enjoy VanGogh's vision, which was considered heretical in its day?  Did James Joyce err in penning _Ulysses_?  Which art is uplifting?  Point to some.  Why?  Is it, by definition, universally uplifting because certain individuals find it so?  Who will be the art &quot;experts&quot;?  The clergy, who as a group are unqualified for this assignment?  Who will &quot;make&quot; the artists?  Whenever religious institutions get involved in policy beyond their venue, there is rampant silliness, and above all, stunted intellectual growth for the individual and society.  This sounds harsher than I really feel about it, but the case must be made.  Please note that my sharp words are not directed at the idea of religion.  One must ignore dumb, dogmatic people in any circumstance, but rather is aimed at the viral INSTITUTION which, as with any other group, has an agenda.  But is is frequently mean-spirited and insensitive.  That's all.  I'm done.

