<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by Amanda on January 01, 1997 at 16:03:30:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="692.html">Re: Unlikely Existence of God</a> posted by Grasshopper on January 01, 1997 at 11:22:41:<p>
<p>: There is absolutely no reason to believe in God, obviously for the lack of proof.  However<br>: I find it equally foolish to rule out the existence of God...There<br>: is no absolute proof so it is better to not to believe one way or the <br>: other--both are equally ridiculous.<p>I agree - I know quite well that if I were to state that "God does not exist" I would be shot down by logic. What I meant with this thread though was that not only do I disbelieve in God but because the evidence is in the direction of the unlikeliness of his existence rather than claiming to be an agnostic which is often seen as putting the existence and non-existence of God on equal footing - I claim to be an atheist because I'm more on the side of the non-existence. By putting in the word "believe" I escape the logical arguments that can be used against me. Badabing.<br>
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
