Posted by Amanda on January 02, 1997 at 03:28:23:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="704.html">Re: Unlikely Existence of God</a> posted by Grasshopper on January 01, 1997 at 20:19:15:<p>
<br>: <br>: We are definately on the same 'side'.  But, just because evidence 'seems' to weigh in <br>: favor of one theory or another I don't think that is reason to lean either way.  Think<br>: how much evidence is unknowable or that you or I just can't comprehend.<br>: respectfully grasshopper<p>Oh, I certainly sway in the direction of the evidence and have no qualms about it - <br>You say you don't believe in anything - I think that's a bit sad and perhaps untrue. I'm quite happy to believe in what I do and when the time comes to change my beliefs it won't be embarassing at all for me - my beliefs and my thinking could do a 180 degree turn tomorrow if new evidence was found to support the opposite of what it does now. I enjoy having educated beliefs that I can support with a lot of provisional truths - I am proud to know my mind and be decided on how I see things. I can't see the benefit at all in not believing in ANYTHING as you say - perhaps you can fill me in. As for noe, I don't think we're at all alike - and if I'm on the side of the evidence and you're not then we're not on the same sides. Happy New Year!
<br>
