Posted by <a href="mailto:kmllr@aol.com">k. miller</a> on December 28, 1996 at 19:58:51:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="585.html">Unlikely Existence of God</a> posted by Amanda on December 26, 1996 at 18:46:35:<p>
The age old question of proving or disproving the existence of a god <br>lies in definition. First all the Western religions are revealed religions<br>dependent on god announcing himself to a Moses, Muhammed etc. Each on<br>one hand is face with scriptural teaching that no one can know god or<br>what he is. RE: book of Job etc.<p>The problem arises when the theist attempts to define God. Thus the endless<br>rantings. ie 'God is all-powerful' followed by 'if god is all powerful<br>can he create a boulder too heavy for even he to lift?'<p>So long as men 'anthropomorhpize ' the god of their choice they<br>immediately provide the material for the dialectic destruction of their <br>concepts. These are the weakest among their respective religions for<br>they lack the faith to simply believe what they believe and go on<br>about their business.<p>The eastern religions are far more critical and methodical in denying<br>the possibilty of God. 
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
