: A hypothesis is an unfounded theory, the evidence for evolution is overwhelming.

: : Again, do you have any evidence of this, other than the THEORY of evolution?  I can &quot;handle the concept&quot; of a randon universe, it's just that no one has given me a good explanation for it.  Saying that, over enough time flying particles from an explosion will organize into a universe full of diverse life forms, is like saying that, over enough time, the dirt in my back yard will form itself into an adobie.

: An adobie is an artifical construct. Haven't you ever heard of trial and error? As I've said before; If we were to start the whole process all over again life on this planet would be completely different in form.
: That is what random means.

