Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on December 17, 1996 at 16:18:08:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="541.html">Re: P.S.</a> posted by Lynn on December 17, 1996 at 14:49:57:<p>
I don't mean to offend anyone, but the Pope's opinions don't carry that much weight with me.<p>But he does speak for the largest denomination of Christians (Around 800,000,000 or so Roman Catholics) and that does carry much weight.<p>: If you can offer me a scientific study that has shown that chaos, of it's own accord, ascends to a state of ordered complexity, I'll shut up.<p>No one can know for sure how the universe had started, not even those who claim it was done by a creator. The only way to know for sure is to die.<p>: The living organism theory is interesting.  I've always pondered whether the universe is a mechanism akin to a clock......one that is winding down, I might add.<p>A clock is an artifical construct, the Universe is a natural one. The Universe is still expanding, so we may still be in the early stage in its life cycle.<br>
