    <center>
      <h1>Re: P.S.</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by Lynn on December 15, 1996 at 17:46:57:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="518.html">Re: P.S.</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on December 15, 1996 at 15:45:46:<p>
: <br>: : : If it does than it is very poorly designed. <g><br>: : <br>: : Oh, so you don't dispute creation science, you just think the Creator did a rotten job. <p>: Yes I do dispute it. It has absolutely no logic or reason to it.<br>: I had said "IF". The Watchmaker (If there is one) is incompetent.<br>: The more we learn of the Universe around us, the more we see how imperfect it is. On the small scale of time that we had seen it does look like it is designed, but over time it turns out not to be.<p><p>I don't think it is any less reasonable to believe the universe was created, than it is to believe everything just appeared and then arranged itself into a complex universe full of complex organisms.  You have not proven your point, nor can you have any idea what discoveries, scientific or otherwise, that will be made beyond your lifetime.  Yes, time will tell, but there's no way you can know what it will say. 
