Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on December 14, 1996 at 01:47:13:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="509.html">Re: Refuting Creation Science</a> posted by Lynn on December 13, 1996 at 12:55:07:<p>
: Hello,<br>: Somehow I feel you have missed the main point of the watchmaker argument.  If we see a watch on the beach, yes we assume a watchmaker made it.  We do not believe that he took all the parts necessary for making the watch, threw them in a bag, shook them up, and a perfectly arranged and working mechanism assembled itself in the bag.  You could shake that baby from now 'til doomsday, and it ain't gonna happen.<p>It also said that any design that we see is in our own minds. The most common pattern recognized is that of a human face, even when there is no face there. We see paterns because we had evolved to see them, saves time in thinking. If it looks like a big and hungry sabretooth tiger the one that flees the quickests survives.<br>
<br>
