<html>
  <head>
    <title>Re: Madalyn Murray O'Hair Petition (?)</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <center>
      <h1>Re: Madalyn Murray O'Hair Petition (?)</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by Amanda on January 10, 1997 at 22:15:36:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="1029.html">Re: Madalyn Murray O'Hair Petition (?)</a> posted by jeff on January 10, 1997 at 18:13:37:<p>
<br>: : The same reason why many Christians would be embarrassed by many TV evangelists.<p>: I guess I never watch any of her show to know.  What were/are they about?<p>: jeff<p>She doesn't have a show. <br>I'm not sure if I'm a mainstream atheist - but I certainly am not embarrassed about what she's done; though I too haven't looked into it that deeply. Her long efforts to get prayer out of school was well done - she deserves some support when she takes on activities like that one. I think the rumour about her trying to get rid of radio broadcasting is a myth - but if she's going to try and get  "in god we trust" off the curency or get rid of the swearing on the bible in court then I'm all for it - and will support it 100%. <br>A lot of myths have been fabricated about her character - perhaps some are true, I do not know...but don't believe everything you here. Some theists also claim voting for Clinton was a sin and those who did so will go to Hell - <br>Theism has a lot of power in this country and some if it is hidden rather well - so, it's good to be as skeptical as possible in this arena.
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
