: 
: : : The same reason why many Christians would be embarrassed by many TV evangelists.

: : I guess I never watch any of her show to know.  What were/are they about?

: : jeff

: She doesn't have a show. 
: I'm not sure if I'm a mainstream atheist - but I certainly am not embarrassed about what she's done; though I too haven't looked into it that deeply. Her long efforts to get prayer out of school was well done - she deserves some support when she takes on activities like that one. I think the rumour about her trying to get rid of radio broadcasting is a myth - but if she's going to try and get  &quot;in god we trust&quot; off the curency or get rid of the swearing on the bible in court then I'm all for it - and will support it 100%. 
: A lot of myths have been fabricated about her character - perhaps some are true, I do not know...but don't believe everything you here. Some theists also claim voting for Clinton was a sin and those who did so will go to Hell - 
: Theism has a lot of power in this country and some if it is hidden rather well - so, it's good to be as skeptical as possible in this arena.

