Comments:<br>
<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: : : Can someone please tell me the name of the originator of the &quot;pyramid power&quot; hoax?
: : I can't remember his name, but you can find in in Richard Noone's book 5/5/2000, which was originaly published as Ice:the Ultimate Disaster. It may not be a hoax, however, G. Patrick Flanagan, who became known in the 70's for patenting pyramid-power devices, is no crank, but is one of America's formost inventor, who was known early on for his genius. There is a new biogrphay of Flanagan, but I can't remember the title. He has stated that when he firts heard about pyramid power, that he did some experiments, and said that they worked, but that they did not work consistently-which may explain the variability of the results of scientific tests.

</textarea>
