: Dear Lori,

: I am equally outraged, but not suprised.  Your employer may also access your medical records and credit history, give you a psychological exam and/or polygraph test, deny employment to you if you smoke, award bonus's according to how thin you are (it's true...a friend of mine works at a place that gives bonus's based on your height/weight ratio), pee in a cup...well, I could go on forever.  It sound's to me like the handwriting thing might be a way of not hiring someone without telling them the real reason why.

: I really have no hope that the trend will change.  

: By the way, just for fun, a lady came to the radio station where I work and did a handwriting analysis of all the disc jockeys.  It's really amazing how accurate she was.  It's a good thing they didn't use this kind of analysis in hiring me.  She said I was so sensitive that I could almost feel what people are thinking.  This is not necessarily a good thing. 

