: Interest in handwriting as an expression of 
: personality is really as old as the use of writing 
: itself.  The school of fixed signs, which emphasize 
: the elements of handwritung - such as the forms of t 
: bars, i dots, hooks, & flourishes, has been abandoned 
: by modern graphoanalysists with the emphasis now on 
: overall aspects. Handwriting must be perveived as a 
: whole and be considered as one piece of the puzzle in 
: a psychological profile.  The &quot;danger&quot; involved in 
: amateur handwriting analysis is that sweeping 
: generalizations based on oversimplifications could 
: lead to discrimination.

