Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on December 25, 1996 at 12:23:19:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="547.html">Re: understanding skepticism/agnosticism</a> posted by Lynn on December 18, 1996 at 14:57:37:<p>
: I would be interested in your opinion about all the eyewitness accounts of God and his dealings with mankind that are recorded in the Bible.   <p>That's an easy answer. What we don't understand we either call the work of God, or destroy. It all depends on one's world view and experiences.<p>As an example we can take Ezekiel's account of being visited by spirits in a wheel-with-in-a-wheel. To him it was a supernatural event, but to us this sounds exactly like an encounter with a UFO and aliens.<br> 
