    <center>
      <h1>understanding skepticism/agnosticism</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by <a href="mailto:lgrant@netonecom.net">Lynn</a> on December 14, 1996 at 17:04:38:<p>
Hello Skeptical Friends,<p>I'm really trying to understand the philosophy of the Skeptics's Society  I've looked in the dictiontionary under "agnostic", "atheist", and "skeptic", yet I haven't found a satisfactory definition.  I'm trying to determine if "skeptics" assume there is some sort of higher power, but that the truth of the matter is unknowable, therefore, unsearchable.
<br>
