<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by grasshopper on January 04, 1997 at 19:13:58:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="827.html">Re: GOD...defined</a> posted by Amanda on January 04, 1997 at 13:26:58:<p>
<br>: Well, put 'em out on the table then - I'll try to give you some evidence for the unlikeliness. This is how we progress - we make claims, back 'em up with evidence, weigh the evidence pro and con, and believe or disbelieve. So, let's play!<p>Ok, I'll try to make up different theories of 'god', so here are a few.<br>Maybe, god creates the universe, arranging the planets...to the minute<br>detail (making it perpetually expand and all)...this god has no intrest <br>in us now...<p>hmm...this is all a hologram...I would concider the maker of the hologram<br>to be 'god' (all definitions)...a very detailed holagram.<p>I made this world (universe we perseve)...just yesterday...to the finest detail<br>your memories and all.<p> There are a few...of course there are many more...I would enjoy arguing these<br>out and I'll make up some more possiblities later.
<br>
