Subject: <input type=text name="subject"value="Re: GOD...defined" size=50><p>
Comments:<br>
<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: 
: : 
: : : Well, put 'em out on the table then - I'll try to give you some evidence for the unlikeliness. This is how we progress - we make claims, back 'em up with evidence, weigh the evidence pro and con, and believe or disbelieve. So, let's play!

: : Ok, I'll try to make up different theories of 'god', so here are a few.
: : Maybe, god creates the universe, arranging the planets...to the minute
: : detail (making it perpetually expand and all)...this god has no intrest 
: : in us now...

: This just sounds like a term being used for the indifferent laws of the Universe - some of which we've discovered. Also, there is some evidence for the Big Bang Theory resulting in the arrangemeent of the galaxies, solar systems, suns and planets - it has more weight than the idea that a guy in th sky was playing with balls and stuff so the belief should sway in the former's direction.
: If you're just using the word &quot;god&quot; to define what we know thus far regarding how the planets came to be - this is a bad word to use - supernaturalism is implied when using the word god.

: : hmm...this is all a hologram...I would concider the maker of the hologram
: : to be 'god' (all definitions)...a very detailed holagram.

: Some psychologists have hypothesized that idea - that this is all a dream but hell, we've got to put a bit of stock in what we sense - We start by realizing that there is more to reality then what goes on in our mind - we use our senses to observe our surroundings and there are certain facts we can discover - we are real and we exist. A God making this all for us is probably the best idea out there but still, no evidence and therefore no belief.

: : I made this world (universe we perseve)...just yesterday...to the finest detail
: : your memories and all.

: Ok, let's see you do it all again. Evidence - none.

: :  There are a few...of course there are many more...I would enjoy arguing these
: : out and I'll make up some more possiblities later.

: The point is you have to back up your claims with evidence and you're not doing that whereas we have evidence for an explanation to this entire universe where a god is not necessary. What belief would you think would help us survive in the cosmos?
: You do have a great imagination though, write some scifi books!

</textarea>
