Posted by <a href="mailto:kakadoo@sprynet.com">Amanda</a> on January 03, 1997 at 14:01:28:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="792.html">GOD...defined</a> posted by grasshopper on January 03, 1997 at 13:45:43:<p>
<br>: I would be interested to hear how you all define the word god...?<p>When I refer to him - he is always a supernatural being. That's how it was defined in the beginning and that should be how it is defined today  - all of these new definitions like the idea that man is god confuses the idea and is another example of our manipulation of language. The way that will end is having us all running around blabbing in our language - not understanding a thing another is saying until we've returned to the caveman type grunt. Hey, maybe it is all a cyclical process - perhaps we've reached the arch and are now headed back from whence we came. I best go buy up some mountain property.
