: I don't know a great deal about human vestigial organs but I know a thing or two
: about them in other species. One example is the Greenland whale. Some of these
: whales have small vestigial hind legs. This is evidence that whales had land
: dwelling ancestors.

: Overall, vestigial organs present a powerful argument for evolution. A good
: question to ask a creationist is, &quot;according 'creation science,' are these
: attributes predicted by your theory?&quot; Evolution can explain it but creationism
: cannot. I tried putting myself in the shoes of a creationist to try to find
: flaws in the argument. I was completely stumped.
