Posted by P Suster on December 11, 1996 at 04:16:02:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="476.html">Whitley Schrieber/Hale-Bopp</a> posted by Sarah Legg on December 09, 1996 at 10:51:56:<p>
: <br>: Hi everyone,<p>: No matter wether you are a believer or a skeptic I am sure you would like Whitley Schrieber's website. Seeing that the man is an "abductee" he does look at things from a very cautious viewpoint. The articles on this page are also a source of interest. A notable example would be the presence of a parculiar object following the comet Hale-Bopp on the edge of our solar-system. The last I have heard, The object is 3 times bigger than the Earth, it is hollow because it has no gravitational effects on the comet or any near by planets. It is also meant to be emmiting radio waves in a set pattern and it also radiates it's own light. Has anyone heard anything more than this? Will this be the close encounter we are waiting for, a hoax or a star?<p>So what's the URL?<br>And where did you get this assertion about the Hale-Bopp hollow-radio-star that's three times the size of earth?<p>I'd bet dollars to doughnuts someone's pulling your leg.  Anything that is three times the size of earth and emits it's own radio waves and light would be far brighter than Hale-Bopp itself and would be front page news.<p>: Sarah. <p>P Suster
