Posted by <a href="mailto:victor7@mindspring.com">Tim Jones</a> on December 21, 1996 at 07:26:12:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="493.html">Re: Whitley Schrieber/Hale-Bopp</a> posted by Michael Sibbernsen on December 11, 1996 at 17:31:14:<p>
<br>: : : <br>: : : Hi everyone,<p>: : : No matter wether you are a believer or a skeptic I am sure you would like Whitley Schrieber's website. Seeing that the man is an "abductee" he does look at things from a very cautious viewpoint. The articles on this page are also a source of interest. A notable example would be the presence of a parculiar object following the comet Hale-Bopp on the edge of our solar-system. The last I have heard, The object is 3 times bigger than the Earth, it is hollow because it has no gravitational effects on the comet or any near by planets. It is also meant to be emmiting radio waves in a set pattern and it also radiates it's own light. Has anyone heard anything more than this? Will this be the close encounter we are waiting for, a hoax or a star?<p>: : So what's the URL?<br>: : And where did you get this assertion about the Hale-Bopp hollow-radio-star that's three times the size of earth?<p>: : I'd bet dollars to doughnuts someone's pulling your leg.  Anything that is three times the size of earth and emits it's own radio waves and light would be far brighter than Hale-Bopp itself and would be front page news.<p>: : : Sarah. <p>: : P Suster<p>: If you are interested in the "mysterious object" following Hale-Bopp, go to the Hale-Bopp page and learn the low down.<p>The whole story came from Art Bell's radio talk show, Coast to Coast Live, which airs from 11:00 PM (PST) to 4:00 AM throughout the US. It's also available live on the net via RealAudio. The show in question, as well as the RealAudio link and other tidbits, is available on Art Bell's web page.  It's interesting, but stretches the limits of credulity.<p>Tim
