Posted by <a href="mailto:royce@dragonet.es">Ron Cave</a> on December 31, 1996 at 11:02:39:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="661.html">Carl Sagan</a> posted by Amanda on December 30, 1996 at 18:30:38:<p>
: When I subscribed to "Skeptic" magazine over the holidays - the woman who took the call mentioned that they were working on a tribute issue on Carl Sagan much like their first issue on Asimov. It will no doubt be a beauty so I thought I'd share the info. He was a great man and I was looking at other great minds that have died such as Asimov and Russell and a host of others and I'm wondering if anyone has any examples of ones that are alive today - fighting to get science out to the people and perhaps minimizing the effects of religion and mysticism in the process? One I can think of is Stephen J. Gould. <p>As with Carlos Javier we are amazed that only today,and through your<br>message board,we heard of the death of Carl Sagon. Here in Spain <br>we didn't hear anything from the B.B.C world service,or satellite Sky news<br>or our local English language newspapers. We met him at the Seattle<br>conference and he was kindness itself. We told him about a lady<br>who lives in the mountains near us who was, what can best be described as a<br>fan. He asked my wife to deliver his best wishe and me to give her a kiss from him.A kind,wise<br>and humourous man and an advocate of reason who will be sorely missed.
<br>
