    <center>
      <h1>Re: Being a person of faith does not mean I leave my brain behind.</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by David on December 24, 1996 at 05:40:45:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="574.html">Re: Being a person of faith does not mean I leave my brain behind.</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on December 24, 1996 at 01:03:32:<p>
: <br>: : I am glad to see someone besides the pompous cycops giving the other side of things on new age and other far out or supernatural topics.  I just want you to know that all of us who believe in someone higher than ourselfs are not flat earthers or creationists.  I am a christian but unlike fundlementalists I don't have the presumption to state that I know the mind of the Allmighty.  I know also that no person can really know what happens after death.  Or if anything happens after death.  But, I certainly hope that all the great people and loving personalitys that have walked the earth don't simply cease to exist. Thank you for the soapbox.  I'm not trying to convert anyone.  Just wanted to say that not all of us people of faith are kooks.<p>: This makes you an agnostic. I'm one as well, I'm also what is called a Secular Humanist.<p>Don't you think that the reason why most people believe in life after death is more through desire rather than fact as you state.  Nobody wants to think that when they die they are gone, nobody wants to think that great men/women or loved ones are simply dead or buried.  Unfortunately all rational evidence points to the fact that everyone is dead and gone.  However it is almost impossible to prove that anything does not exist (try and prove that fairies and goblins don't) so it ultimately comes down to your own belief system.  If you were just about any other religion other than Christian you would probably believe in reincarnation for everyone (not just Christ).<br>
