Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on December 24, 1996 at 01:03:32:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="571.html">Being a person of faith does not mean I leave my brain behind.</a> posted by stephen snead on December 23, 1996 at 11:20:39:<p>
<br>: I am glad to see someone besides the pompous cycops giving the other side of things on new age and other far out or supernatural topics.  I just want you to know that all of us who believe in someone higher than ourselfs are not flat earthers or creationists.  I am a christian but unlike fundlementalists I don't have the presumption to state that I know the mind of the Allmighty.  I know also that no person can really know what happens after death.  Or if anything happens after death.  But, I certainly hope that all the great people and loving personalitys that have walked the earth don't simply cease to exist. Thank you for the soapbox.  I'm not trying to convert anyone.  Just wanted to say that not all of us people of faith are kooks.<p>This makes you an agnostic. I'm one as well, I'm also what is called a Secular Humanist.<br>
