Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on December 24, 1996 at 15:54:02:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="575.html">Re: Being a person of faith does not mean I leave my brain behind.</a> posted by David on December 24, 1996 at 05:40:45:<p>
: Don't you think that the reason why most people believe in life after death is more through desire rather than fact as you state.  Nobody wants to think that when they die they are gone, nobody wants to think that great men/women or loved ones are simply dead or buried.  Unfortunately all rational evidence points to the fact that everyone is dead and gone.  However it is almost impossible to prove that anything does not exist (try and prove that fairies and goblins don't) so it ultimately comes down to your own belief system.  If you were just about any other religion other than Christian you would probably believe in reincarnation for everyone (not just Christ).<p>When it comes to something like this reason and logic go out the window.<br>BTW, before Vatican I reincarnation was a major part of Christianity.<p>
