In Reply to: <a href="752.html">Re: Scripture (was: Unlikely Existence of God)</a> posted by Lynn on January 02, 1997 at 12:45:26:<p>
: The Jews were NOT practicing genocide.  People throw that word around too loosely. These commands pertained to people living within the Israelite community who were guilty of trying to entice others to worship false gods...  <p>If it sounds like a duck....<p>What would YOU call it?<p>One may die for one's beliefs, religious or otherwise, but it is wrong to <br>kill for them.<br>
